# MC40 using Broadcast Intent.

Sample appcelerator project running on MC40 devices.

<sdk-version>3.4.1.GA</sdk-version>

## How to configure your Appcelerator Project

Add the intent filter to your MainActivity, can be something as this in your `tiapp.xml` file:

~~~~
    <activity android:name=".McActivity" android:label="@string/app_name" android:theme="@style/Theme.Titanium" android:configChanges="keyboardHidden|orientation|screenSize">
	<intent-filter>
	    <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN"/>
	    <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER"/>
	</intent-filter>
	<intent-filter>
	    <action android:name="com.yourdomain.yourProject.RECVR"/>
	    <category android:name="android.intent.category.DEFAULT"/>
	</intent-filter>
    </activity>
~~~~

## How to configure your DataWedge

Create a new Profile and use the same intent action name defined in your `tiapp.xml`. Set the new
Profile:

*Profile enabled (checked)
*Applications - Associated apps (link your appcelerator project using org.appcelerator.titanium.TiActivity)
*Barcode Input - Enabled (checked)
*Intent Output - Enabled (checked)
*Intent action needs to be set as:

~~~~
com.yourdomain.yourProject.RECVR
~~~~

Leave the Intent Category in blank and set the Intent delivery as:

* Broadcast intent

